  <!-- WHY ANNUAL SERVICE outcomes first -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Why Every Liverpool Boiler Needs an Annual Service</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Carbon monoxide safety. Warranty protection. Lower bills. Early fault detection. An annual service costs £120 and protects everything that matters.</p>
      <div style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-pros">
          <h3 style="text-align:center;">What an Annual Service Protects</h3>
          <ul class="pf-check-list">
            <li>Carbon monoxide safety. A serviced boiler has its flue and combustion checked by a Gas Safe engineer. A faulty flue or cracked heat exchanger leaking CO has no smell, no colour and no warning. Annual servicing is the only way to know your boiler is not producing CO</li>
            <li>Manufacturer warranty maintained. Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Ideal and Baxi all require annual servicing by a Gas Safe engineer to keep the warranty valid. Missing one year can void a 10-year warranty entirely</li>
            <li>Lower gas bills. A serviced boiler runs up to 10 to 15% more efficiently than an unserviced one. At current gas prices that is a real saving every month, and significantly more than the cost of the service over a year</li>
            <li>Early fault detection before breakdown. A Gas Safe engineer catches developing faults before they cause a mid-winter breakdown. A worn part identified in October costs far less than an emergency callout in January</li>
            <li>Inhibitor levels replenished. Corrosion inhibitor protects your radiators, pipework and heat exchanger. It degrades over time and drops below effective levels. Every service includes an inhibitor test and top-up</li>
            <li>Legal compliance for landlords. Liverpool landlords are legally required to have gas appliances serviced annually and hold a valid CP12. See <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HSE landlord gas safety obligations</a></li>
            <li>Annual reminder included. We add you to our reminder list and contact you when your next service is due. You never accidentally miss a year and risk voiding your warranty</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="pf-info-bar" style="margin-top:2rem;">
          <div style="display:flex;flex-direction:column;gap:0.5rem;">
            <div style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--text);">✓ The <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/domestic/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Health and Safety Executive</a> recommends annual boiler servicing for all domestic gas appliances.</div>
            <div style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--text);">✓ <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk/help-and-advice/is-my-home-safe/carbon-monoxide/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safe Register</a> states a faulty boiler is one of the leading causes of carbon monoxide incidents in UK homes.</div>
            <div style="font-size:0.85rem;color:var(--text);">✓ We follow the <a href="https://www.hhic.org.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Heating and Hot Water Industry Council (HHIC)</a> service checklist on every visit. All major boiler manufacturers specify this standard for warranty-compliant servicing.</div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WHAT IS CHECKED single column -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2 style="text-align:center;">What Our Gas Safe Engineers Check During a Liverpool Boiler Service</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub" style="text-align:center;">A thorough 10-point HHIC inspection covering every aspect of your boiler's safety and performance. Completed in 45 minutes to 1 hour.</p>

      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Flue gas analysis</strong><p>Combustion gases tested to confirm correct and safe burning. Abnormal readings indicate incomplete combustion and potential carbon monoxide risk.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Gas pressure and flow rate</strong><p>Gas supply pressure and flow rate checked to confirm the boiler is receiving the correct supply. Low pressure causes lockouts and poor performance.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Burner and heat exchanger</strong><p>Burner removed and inspected for debris and damage. Heat exchanger checked for corrosion, cracking or sludge that would reduce efficiency.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Flue integrity and seals</strong><p>Flue inspected along its full route. Confirmed intact, correctly sealed and safely discharging combustion gases. A leaking flue seal is a carbon monoxide risk.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Safety devices tested</strong><p>Pressure relief valve, overheat thermostat and gas valve all tested. Each confirmed to operate correctly and shut the boiler down safely under fault conditions.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>System pressure checked</strong><p>System pressure checked and topped up if required. Low pressure is a common lockout cause and reduces heating efficiency across the whole system.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Inhibitor level tested and topped up</strong><p>Inhibitor concentration tested. Low inhibitor accelerates corrosion and sludge build-up. Topped up to the correct level as standard on every service.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Controls and programmer</strong><p>Thermostat, programmer and any zone valves checked for correct operation. A faulty zone valve causes uneven heating even with a fully functioning boiler.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Magnetic filter cleaned</strong><p>If a magnetic filter is fitted, cleaned as part of the service. A blocked filter reduces flow and strains the pump. Condition noted and replacement advised if needed.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Full function test and Benchmark updated</strong><p>Full heating and hot water cycle run to confirm correct operation. Benchmark commissioning record updated with service date and findings. Certificate emailed same day.</p></div></div>
      </div>

      <div style="background:#fff7ed;border:1px solid #fed7aa;border-left:4px solid #f97316;border-radius:10px;padding:1rem 1.25rem;margin-top:2rem;text-align:center;">
        <p style="color:#7c2d12;font-size:0.88rem;margin:0;font-weight:600;">If we find anything during the service, we explain it clearly and give you a written repair quote before any additional work begins. You are never charged for work you have not approved.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- WARRANTY PROTECTION -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f1f5f9;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Protect Your Boiler Warranty with an Annual Service</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Missing an annual service can void your manufacturer warranty completely. Here is what each major brand requires.</p>
      <div class="pf-who-grid" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Worcester Bosch. Up to 10 years</strong><p><a href="https://www.worcester-bosch.co.uk/support/warranty-and-guarantee" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Worcester Bosch</a> requires annual servicing by a Gas Safe registered engineer and a completed Benchmark certificate. Missing a service invalidates the warranty regardless of when the boiler was installed.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Vaillant. Up to 10 years</strong><p><a href="https://www.vaillant.co.uk/homeowners/support-and-spares/warranty/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Vaillant</a> requires annual servicing and the service must be recorded in the Benchmark commissioning checklist. Failure to service annually voids the extended warranty.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Ideal Boilers. Up to 10 years</strong><p>Ideal Boilers require annual servicing by a Gas Safe registered engineer. The service record must be retained and available for any warranty claim. We update the record on every visit.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-who-item pf-who-yes"><span class="pf-who-icon">✓</span><div><strong>Baxi. Up to 7 years</strong><p>Baxi requires annual servicing by a qualified Gas Safe engineer. An unserviced boiler that develops a fault as a direct result of lack of maintenance will not be covered under the manufacturer warranty.</p></div></div>
      </div>
      <div style="background:#fef2f2;border:1px solid #fecaca;border-left:4px solid #dc2626;border-radius:10px;padding:1rem 1.25rem;margin-top:2rem;text-align:center;">
        <p style="color:#7f1d1d;font-size:0.88rem;margin:0;font-weight:600;">A single missed annual service can void a 10-year Worcester Bosch or Vaillant warranty entirely. One annual service at £120 costs far less than a single out-of-warranty repair, let alone a new boiler.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <!-- SIGNS -->
  <section class="pf-section" style="background:#f8fafc;">
    <div class="container">
      <h2>Signs Your Liverpool Boiler Needs Servicing Now</h2>
      <p class="pf-sub">Do not wait for the annual reminder if your boiler is showing any of these signs. We can often attend the same day.</p>
      <div class="pf-signs" style="margin-top:2rem;">
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Boiler making unusual noises</strong><p>Banging, kettling, gurgling or whistling sounds indicate developing faults. Often caused by scale build-up, low inhibitor or a failing component that is far cheaper to address at a service than after a full breakdown.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Boiler locking out repeatedly</strong><p>A boiler that keeps shutting itself down is detecting a fault. Error codes point to the cause. A diagnostic visit identifies the underlying issue before it causes a complete failure.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Yellow or orange pilot flame</strong><p>A healthy gas flame is blue. Yellow or orange indicates incomplete combustion and a potential carbon monoxide risk. Stop using the boiler immediately. If you suspect CO, call <a href="https://cadentgas.com" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Cadent Gas on 0800 111 999</a> first, then call us.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Boiler pressure keeps dropping</strong><p>A system that repeatedly loses pressure indicates a leak in the heating circuit. This can damage the pump and heat exchanger if left unaddressed. A service will identify the source.</p></div></div>
        <div class="pf-sign"><div><strong>Hot water but no heating, or heating but no hot water</strong><p>Partial failures usually indicate a zone valve fault, diverter valve issue or thermostat problem. All of these components are checked as part of our standard service.</p></div></div>
