      <div class="pf-faq">
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">COST</span>&nbsp; How much does a boiler service cost in Liverpool?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A standard annual boiler service costs £120 fixed price, including the full HHIC inspection and service certificate emailed the same day. A combined service and CP12 gas safety certificate costs £175 in a single visit. A fault diagnosis visit costs £95. No call-out fee, no hidden extras on any of these.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">LEGAL</span>&nbsp; Is a boiler service a legal requirement?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>For homeowners, an annual boiler service is not a legal requirement but is strongly recommended by the <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/domestic/" target="_blank" rel="noopener">HSE</a>, <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safe Register</a> and all major manufacturers as a warranty condition. For landlords it is a legal requirement under the <a href="https://www.hse.gov.uk/gas/landlords/index.htm" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safety Regulations 1998</a>. Landlords must hold a valid CP12 and provide a copy to tenants within 28 days of issue.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">HOW OFTEN</span>&nbsp; How often should I service my boiler?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Every year without exception. All major boiler manufacturers require annual servicing by a Gas Safe registered engineer to keep the warranty valid. Missing a single year can void a 10-year warranty entirely. A serviced boiler also runs up to 15% more efficiently than an unserviced one. We add you to our annual reminder list after your first service so you never miss a year.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">DIY</span>&nbsp; Can I service my own boiler?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>No. A gas boiler service must be carried out by a <a href="https://www.gassaferegister.co.uk" target="_blank" rel="noopener">Gas Safe registered engineer</a>. This is a legal requirement under the Gas Safety Regulations. Attempting to service a gas boiler yourself is illegal and dangerous. Always verify your engineer's Gas Safe registration number before any gas work is carried out on your property.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">FAULTS</span>&nbsp; What happens if a fault is found during the service?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>If we find a fault or a developing issue during the service, the engineer explains exactly what was found and provides a written repair quote before any additional work is carried out. We never start repair work without your explicit approval. You are never charged for work you have not agreed to. If a repair is needed, we can often carry it out on the same visit.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-navy">TIME</span>&nbsp; How long does a boiler service take?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>A standard boiler service takes between 45 minutes and 1 hour. A combined service and gas safety certificate takes around 60 to 75 minutes. We work efficiently and leave no mess behind.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-green">WARRANTY</span>&nbsp; Does an annual service protect my boiler warranty?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Worcester Bosch, Vaillant, Ideal and Baxi all require annual servicing by a Gas Safe registered engineer and an updated Benchmark certificate. Missing a single annual service can void a 10-year warranty entirely. We follow the HHIC checklist and update the Benchmark record on every service visit.</p></div></details>
        <details class="pf-faq-item"><summary><span class="pf-faq-tag pf-tag-orange">LANDLORDS</span>&nbsp; Do you provide the gas safety certificate landlords need?</summary><div class="pf-faq-body"><p>Yes. Our combined service and CP12 gas safety certificate costs £175 in a single visit. Both documents are emailed the same day. The CP12 is accepted by all Liverpool letting agents, Liverpool City Council HMO licensing and the <a href="https://www.nrla.org.uk/resources/gas-safety" target="_blank" rel="noopener">NRLA</a>. We service portfolio landlords across all Liverpool postcodes and can coordinate tenant access.</p></div></details>
